Creapiing looked up to see her apprentice hesistantly standing at the door. She had only just finished reading an ultimatum from the Lodge of the Dragon Claw, but had a few moments before she wanted to move on to the next paper on her stack that awaited her attention. She motioned for her apprentice to approach her.<br>
<br>
The apprentice moved forward, carefully averting his eyes as all the good ones did. He carefully held out a scroll and waited for Creapiing to take it, bowing and exiting when she did.<br>
<br>
Carefully she unrolled the scroll, recognizing the seal at once. Reaper, she read, you have charged me with the task of discovering where each member of the harvest draws their hate, their strength from...Here is the story of Kalael.<br>
<br>
Creapiing slowly read the missive, then penned at the bottom of the scroll--Watch this one, his hatred is great, and who knows what other powers he may discover within himself when he is stronger. She rang a bell for her apprentice to return, handed him the scroll, and dismissed him.<br>
